The paper deals with the task of mammographic mass segmentation using deep convolutional neural networks and conditional random fields. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of adversarial training to control over-fitting, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging (cs.MM) and uses deep learning techniques for the task, which could also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of multiple models and their fusion to improve segmentation results, which could also fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
